# Deployment Checklist

## Pre-Deployment

### Environment Setup
- [ ] Node.js >= 18.0.0 installed
- [ ] npm >= 9.0.0 installed
- [ ] Dependencies installed (`npm install`)
- [ ] `.env` file created from `.env.example`
- [ ] `PRIVATE_KEY` configured in `.env`
- [ ] `ETHERSCAN_API_KEY` configured in `.env`

### Wallet Setup
- [ ] MetaMask installed and configured
- [ ] Account has sufficient Sepolia ETH (> 0.01 ETH)
- [ ] Private key matches the funded account
- [ ] Network set to Sepolia in MetaMask

### Code Quality
- [ ] All tests passing (`npm run test`)
- [ ] Code compiled without errors (`npm run compile`)
- [ ] Linting passed (`npm run lint`)
- [ ] Code formatted (`npm run format`)

## Deployment

### Compile
- [ ] Run `npm run compile`
- [ ] Verify artifacts generated in `artifacts/`
- [ ] No compilation warnings or errors

### Test
- [ ] Run `npm run test`
- [ ] All tests passing
- [ ] Coverage acceptable (`npm run test:coverage`)

### Deploy
- [ ] Run `npm run deploy`
- [ ] Deployment successful
- [ ] Contract address saved
- [ ] Transaction hash recorded
- [ ] Deployment info saved in `deployments/sepolia-deployment.json`

## Post-Deployment

### Verification
- [ ] Run `npm run verify`
- [ ] Contract verified on Etherscan
- [ ] Source code visible on Etherscan
- [ ] Verification link saved

### Testing on Network
- [ ] Run `npm run interact`
- [ ] Contract state retrieved successfully
- [ ] Owner address correct
- [ ] Initial values correct

### Documentation
- [ ] Update `README.md` with contract address (if needed)
- [ ] Save deployment information
- [ ] Document any issues encountered
- [ ] Update team on deployment status

## Security

### Access Control
- [ ] Owner address is correct
- [ ] No unauthorized access possible
- [ ] Private keys secured
- [ ] `.env` not committed to git

### Contract Review
- [ ] Contract functions working as expected
- [ ] No critical bugs found
- [ ] Gas costs acceptable
- [ ] Security best practices followed

## Monitoring

### Initial Setup
- [ ] Bookmark Etherscan contract page
- [ ] Monitor first few transactions
- [ ] Check events are emitted correctly
- [ ] Verify state changes as expected

### Long-term
- [ ] Set up transaction monitoring
- [ ] Monitor gas costs
- [ ] Track contract usage
- [ ] Plan for upgrades (if needed)

## Rollback Plan

### If Issues Found
- [ ] Document the issue
- [ ] Do NOT use the contract
- [ ] Review the problem
- [ ] Fix code and redeploy
- [ ] Update documentation

## Final Checks

- [ ] Contract deployed successfully
- [ ] Contract verified on Etherscan
- [ ] All tests passing
- [ ] Documentation updated
- [ ] Team notified
- [ ] Deployment info backed up

